### [Isaiah Chapter 50](../../../bib/kjv/isa050.htm#001.md)

[Isaiah](../../../bib/kjv/isa001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">isa 50:0</span></span>

Overview

[Isa 50:1](../../../bib/kjv/isa050.htm#001.md), Christ shews that the
dereliction of the Jews is not to be imputed to him, by his ability to
save; [Isa 50:5](../../../bib/kjv/isa050.htm#005.md), by his obedience in
that work; [Isa 50:7](../../../bib/kjv/isa050.htm#007.md), and by his
confidence in that assistance; [Isa
50:10](../../../bib/kjv/isa050.htm#010.md), An exhortation to trust in God,
and not in ourselves.

